Our primary focus is on prevention of any accidental releases.  However, we have strong emergency response capabilities to back-up our prevention activities.  We use this combination of prevention programs and emergency response capability to help ensure the safety of our employees and the public as well as protection of the environment. 
This document provides a brief overview of the comprehensive risk management activities that we have designed and implemented, including:

o A description of our facility and use of substances regulated by EPA's Risk Management Program   
   regulation;
o A summary of results from our assessment of the potential off-site consequences from accidental 
   chemical releases;
o An overview of our accidental release prevention programs;
o An overview of our emergency response program;
o A five-year history of accidental releases of chemicals regulated by EPA's RMP rule;
o An overview of planned improvements at the facility to help prevent accidental chemical releases from 
   occurring and adversely affecting our employees, the public, and the environment;
o The certifications that EPA's RMP rule requires us to provide; and
o The detailed information (called data elements) about our risk management program.


Site Identification and Regulated Substances

The DuPont Dow Elastomers Beaumont Plant is part of a larger site called the Beaumont Industrial Park.  This industrial park is located on Highway 347 in Beaumont, Texas. Our facilities at the Beaumont Industrial Park presently employ 380 people who live and work in Jefferson County and vicinity.  The two manufacturing facilities located at the site have been in operation since 1957, producing high performance products, such as, Hypalon. and Nordel. specialty elastomers.  

